<body>
<h1>Engine Displacement Calculation By Bowling</h1>
<a href=3D"http://www.efn.org/~msayer">Marc Sayer</a> suggested this progra=
m,
which has lots of utility.  The following calculates engine displacement
based on piston size and engine stroke.  For convenience, the piston diamet=
er
is broken up to two inputs, one for the stock piston size, and the other
the oversize number.  The code simply adds the values together, so one
can put in the actual piston size in one field, and zero in another if desi=
red.
Output lists in Cubic Inch Displacement, Liters, and CC.
<p>
</p><hr>

<form action=3D"http://www.bgsoflex.com/cgi-bin/displacement.cgi">

<h1>User Inputs:</h1>
<p>
Number Of Cylinders:                            <input name=3D"ncyl" size=
=3D"5" maxlength=3D"5" value=3D"8">=20
</p><p>
Piston Stock Diameter:                          <input name=3D"diam" size=
=3D"5" maxlength=3D"5" value=3D"4.0">=20
</p><p>
Piston Oversize Value:                          <input name=3D"osize" size=
=3D"5" maxlength=3D"5" value=3D"0.0">=20
</p><p>
Engine Stroke:                                  <input name=3D"stroke" size=
=3D"5" maxlength=3D"5" value=3D"3.48">=20
</p><p>
Units For Inputs:
<select name=3D"mode">
<option>Inches
</option><option>Centimeters
</option><option>Millimeters
</option></select>
</p><p>
Press this button to submit a computation:=20
<input type=3D"submit" value=3D"Compute"> </p><p>

To reset the form input: <input type=3D"reset" value=3D"Reset">

</p></form>

